-- 2012-06-12T11:53:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/foreign-investors-buy-net-2-14-billion-rupees-of-indian-stocks.html
Overseas  investors  bought a net  2.14
billion rupees  ($38.8 million) of Indian stocks yesterday,
raising total investment in equities this year to 419.2 billion
rupees, according to the nationâ€™s market regulator.  Foreigners bought 16.2 billion rupees of shares and sold
14.1 billion rupees, the Securities & Exchange Board of India
said on its  website  today. Foreign funds bought a net 7.53
billion rupees of bonds, taking total inflow into debt this year
to 199.8 billion rupees, the data  show .  The regulator provides data on shares bought and sold by
large investors, including trades in the primary and secondary
markets, with a delay of at least a day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
